parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake caliper can cause excessive brake wear, leading to potential brake failure, which can increase the risk of accidents and put the safety of the driver and others at risk.
symptoms: Brake caliper freezes
excessive brake wear
brake pedal slowly goes to the floorboards
repeated pumping of the brake pedal is required to prevent running into the car in front.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The master cylinder leak down can cause the brake pedal to slowly go to the floorboards, making it difficult to stop the vehicle, which can increase the risk of accidents and put the safety of the driver and others at risk.
symptoms: Brake pedal slowly goes to the floorboards
repeated pumping of the brake pedal is required to prevent running into the car in front
master cylinder leak down gets progressively worse with time.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or become inoperable, leading to safety risks, especially if it occurs in traffic or at an intersection. Additionally, it can cause damage to the battery and other electrical components, resulting in costly repairs.
symptoms: Dashboard warning lights illuminate
vehicle stalls or becomes inoperable
headlights and electrical engine remain on even after the vehicle is turned off
vehicle will not start
battery damage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Inaccurate vehicle information can lead to safety concerns and difficulties in resolving issues, while poor customer service can cause frustration and delay in addressing problems.

manufacturer and dealership having incorrect addresses

being referred between manufacturer and dealership with no resolution.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Water Ingress and Electronic Module Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water ingress into the vehicle can cause electronic module failure, leading to sudden loss of power and engine malfunction, which can result in accidents, especially on busy highways.
symptoms: Sudden loss of power
engine malfunction
vehicle stalls or shuts down without warning
unknown water leaks in the vehicle
faulty module under the back seat.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Lack of Recall Notification for Known Water Leak Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure to notify vehicle owners of known water leak issues can lead to delayed or missed repairs, increasing the risk of accidents and engine malfunction.
symptoms: No recall notification received despite known water leak issues in the vehicle model
water leaks in the vehicle
unknown water leaks in the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Sensor Failure and Tank Pressure Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel sensor and tank pressure issues can cause the fuel tank to not release properly, making it difficult or impossible to refill the gas tank, which can lead to safety issues, such as running out of fuel on the road, and inconvenience to the driver.
symptoms: The gas flap is difficult or impossible to open
the fuel tank does not release pressure properly
the fuel sensor fails
the vehicle runs out of fuel unexpectedly
the fuel tank cannot be refilled.
